            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1638807239557-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and cook for a further 2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1638807242617-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1638807242617-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1638807242617-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1638807242617-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1638807242617-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1638807245450-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1638807245450-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1638807245450-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1638807245450-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1638807245450-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in the <strong>tomato paste </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> drained cannellini beans</strong>,<strong> chopped sweet potato</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15 min or until the sweet potato is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
